	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          What I did... <br>  <br> I bought an external HD enclosure and bought a normal HD to go inside. You can find these enclosures at Fry's. Usually you choose a USB 2.0 or Firewire flavor, they shouldn't cost more than $40. <br>  <br> If you want specific recommendations, I just say try something and make sure there's a return policy if you're not satisified. <br>  <br> Remote backups... No idea I have a couple DVD-RW's and I just keep my sensitive docs and other porn on those (2 copies). <br>  <br> -Len. 
          
