	    <td  bgcolor="dedede"  valign="top" class="msg" width="100%" >
         
          Good suggestion, I keep a 256Meg flash drive on my keychain, nice for just my documents, gets a little crowded if I try downloading lots of stuff to take home with me, but it's nice and fast. On newer systems you can even boot your system from the flash drive if you need emergency boot stuff. <br>  <br> Probably just add up all the stuff you have to store, double that number and if it comes under 512Megs that's not too bad a suggestion. If it's above that then go with the HD, a 1 gig memory stick might cost a bit. 
          
